    "Similarly, for classes k-1 and k+1, the bitlines with the maximal current will be k-1 and k+1.",
    "A schematic representation of this behaviour is presented in Fig. 20.",
    "As seen, the case of misclassified images exists, corresponding to the highest current for an image from class k not being provided by column k. The selection of the highest current at a given time t is performed ex situ (i.e.",
    "via MATLAB) by processing the recorded current traces.",
    "This could be easily implemented on-chip by including a softargmax() 148 CMOS circuit as those discussed in Section SoftArgMax function (block 8)."
